; GENERATOR simplification: `dead` has no consumers, so the per-result body
; of its add_i32 application becomes a no-op and the pure GENERATOR is
; deleted outright. The `q` application stays live, and the top-down checker
; for the bound query `lookup` re-applies add_i32 with the empty branch as
; the absent path; when that branch does nothing it is pruned but the result
; branch must keep working.

#functor add_i32(bound i32 L, bound i32 R, free i32 S) @range(.).

#message m(i32 A).
#local dead(i32 S).
#local q(i32 A, i32 S).
#query lookup(bound i32 A, bound i32 S).
#query getq(bound i32 A, free i32 S).

dead(S) : m(A), add_i32(A, 1, S).
q(A, S) : m(A), add_i32(A, 1, S).
lookup(A, S) : q(A, S).
getq(A, S) : q(A, S).
